1
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,920
查理
Charlie!

2
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,730
我担心你赶不上这班巴士
I wasn't so sure you'd be on the bus.

3
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:28,550
不想让你的白人弟兄们误以为
Didn't want your white brothers thinking

4
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:31,100
你是我们族里最优秀的人才
you were the best we had.

5
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:19,180
所罗门群岛 1943年

6
00:05:32,330 --> 00:05:34,060
小心
Watch out!

7
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:41,230
我的手
My hand!

8
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,720
他妈的
Goddamn!

9
00:06:05,090 --> 00:06:08,360
快没子弹了，我们得快走
We're running out of ammo. We gotta get out of here.

10
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,630
前进
Move!

11
00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:34,050
过来
Come on!

12
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:39,150
过来，你办得到的
Come on, you can do it! Come on!

13
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,650
完全没弹药了，恩得斯， 我们没弹药了
We got nothin', Enders! We're out of ammo!

14
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:04,180
乔伊，我们不该再平白牺牲，现在撤退还来得及
Joe... Nobody else needs to die. We can go! We can get outta here!

15
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:11,920
我们身负任务
We got orders!

16
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:15,590
上面要我们守住这个点，我们就得死守在这里
They told us to hold the position! And that's what we're gonna do!

17
00:07:25,670 --> 00:07:28,660
起来，阿兵哥，死守下去
Get up, marine! Hold the goddamn position!

18
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:35,310
拼啦
Come on!

19
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:38,210
趴下
Get down!

20
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,660
汤米
Tommy.

21
00:07:46,530 --> 00:07:48,720
该死的家伙
Goddamn you!

22
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:56,360
不
Oh, no! No!

23
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:11,710
- 比尔 - 我没子弹了
- Bill! - I'm out.

24
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:18,280
过来
Come on! Come on!

25
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:34,640
你他妈的，乔伊・恩得斯
Goddamn you, Joe Enders.

26
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:38,170
不
No... No!

27
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:42,910
不
No!

28
00:08:54,590 --> 00:08:56,620
右手举起来
Raise your right hand.

29
00:08:56,760 --> 00:09:00,320
- 我…说自己的名字… - 我，班亚吉…
- I... State your full name... - I, Ben Yahzee...

30
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:04,800
彭德尔顿营 加利福尼亚

31
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:09,640
兹誓言支持并保护美国宪法
..do solemnly swear to support and defend the constitution of the US...

32
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:14,840
抵御任何敌人，不论国内或国外…
..against all enemies, foreign and domestic... ..against all enemies, foreign and domestic...

33
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:18,450
日本人称之为“箱子”，谁知道“坦克”的密码？
Jap Ha-Go. Who can give me the code word for "tank"?

34
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:29,290
你们想成为密码战士
Come on. You boys wanna be codetalkers.

35
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:32,190
那就要有脑袋啊，快想
Show me some brains. Think!

36
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:34,760
我们怎么说坦克？
What do we call a tank?

37
00:09:39,010 --> 00:09:40,530
Chay-da-gahi.

38
00:09:43,710 --> 00:09:46,040
乌龟，很好
Tortoise. Good.

39
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,440
大炮，密码？
Artillery. Code word?

40
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:56,410
请说密码，白马二等兵
In code. Private Whitehorse.

41
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:59,180
Be-al-doh-tso-lani?

42
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:02,720
很好
Very good.

43
00:10:02,860 --> 00:10:04,760
日本零式战机，密码？
Japanese Zero. Code word?

44
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:09,220
肯尼欧湾美国海军医院 1943

45
00:10:40,070 --> 00:10:42,900
现在撤退还来得及
We can go! We can get outta here!

46
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,100
上面要我们守住这个点
They told us to hold the position!

47
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:01,920
天气真好啊
Nice day, huh?

48
00:11:02,660 --> 00:11:04,320
乔伊？
Joe?

49
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,730
乔伊？
Joe.

50
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:24,710
你根本没听到我在说话，对吧？
Didn't hear a word, did you?

51
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:28,440
男人碰到美女不都是这样
That's what happens to a man when he's talking to a beautiful woman.

52
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:31,740
你不读我的唇语才会这样
It happens when you're not watching my lips, Joe.

53
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,060
你看我
Watch this.

54
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:02,000
你还没康复，骗不了人的
You're a mess, Joe. You're not fooling anybody.

55
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:04,510
不，丽塔，他才是还没康复
No, Rita. He's a mess.

56
00:12:07,050 --> 00:12:08,540
我每天都在康复中
I'm getting better every day.

57
00:12:08,690 --> 00:12:12,850
你中耳破损，平衡感不正常
You got a perforated eardrum, Enders. Your equilibrium's all screwy.

58
00:12:12,990 --> 00:12:15,980
站都站不起来怎么重回战场
You can't go back to war if you can't stand up.

59
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:20,030
走吧，胜利不会从天上掉下来
Let's go, marines. This war ain't gonna wait forever. Let's go.

60
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,490
乔伊？
Joe...

61
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,650
为什么你不好好留下来？
Why don't you just stay here, Joe?

62
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:51,220
总得有人留下来陪妇女救护团
Somebody's gotta keep the WAVES company.

63
00:12:52,770 --> 00:12:54,930
你到底帮不帮我？
Are you gonna help me or not?

64
00:13:40,980 --> 00:13:42,170
丧失听力

65
00:13:48,190 --> 00:13:49,750
改善很多了
Marked improvement.

66
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:52,780
他左耳情况比较差吗？
And his left ear is the worse of the two?

67
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:15,950
好得真快
It's... amazing.

68
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:29,690
TBY型的范围比不上TBX
TBY hasn't got the range of the TBX.

69
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:33,360
所以讯号可能要分程传递
So you may need a relay to get your transmission to command post.

70
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:37,770
但重点是压力下的速度与精准
But what it really comes down to is speed and accuracy under pressure.

71
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,900
开始解读
Transcribe now.

72
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:43,800
维多，这是X光，完毕
Victor, Victor. This is X-ray. Over.

73
00:14:51,780 --> 00:14:54,380
可恶，我方弟兄遭炮火攻击
Damn it! We got a unit under fire!

74
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:56,650
伤亡惨重
We're losing men.

75
00:14:56,790 --> 00:14:58,980
请解读这段讯息
I need this message decrypted.

76
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:10,040
“请求炮火支援，目标在119，B15”
"Request fire support. We have target at one-one-niner, Baker one-five."

77
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:13,140
“碉堡有重机枪，请立刻开火”
"Pillbox with heavy machine gun. Fire at will."

78
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:20,570
初学者手气好
Beginner's luck.

79
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,640
换你了，大哥
You're up, mac.

80
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:59,380
- 恩得斯下士报到，长官 - 稍息
- Corporal Enders reporting, sir. - At ease.

81
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:08,720
你的表现相当不错，下士
You've done well as a marine, Corporal.

82
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:11,960
比从军前的行为好多了
Better than you did as a civilian.

83
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:16,330
偷窃撞毁机车，遭高中勒令退学
Stole a motorbike, crashed it. Got kicked out of high school.

84
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:21,870
袭击并殴打克里宾欧唐诺神父
Assault and battery... on one Father Crispin O'Donnell?

85
00:16:23,540 --> 00:16:25,530
连教士都打？
A priest?

86
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:30,380
他是齐纳主教高中副校长兼训导主任
Assistant principal at Archbishop Keenan High School, sir, and head disciplinarian.

87
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:33,750
我以前念的是公立学校
Public-school boy myself.

88
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:37,520
训练中心时还是小错不断
Some minor problems in boot.

89
00:16:38,730 --> 00:16:41,220
在上海获颁最佳勇气奖
A commendation for valor in Shanghai.

90
00:16:41,690 --> 00:16:44,820
死守所罗门群岛表现杰出
And you made a hell of a stand on the Solomons.

91
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,990
那儿很苦吧？
Tough bit of business there, huh?

92
00:16:47,730 --> 00:16:49,360
相当艰苦，长官
Pretty tough, sir.

93
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,740
可是，你想再回去？
But you're prepared to jump right back into it?

94
00:16:53,010 --> 00:16:54,670
是的，长官，非常想
Yes, sir. Very much so.

95
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,100
非常想
Very much so.

96
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,800
可是…
Well...

97
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:07,380
我们的密码全遭日军破解
The Japs have pretty much busted every code we've thrown at 'em, Corporal.

98
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:10,510
你在所罗门群岛的弟兄，因密码被破解全部阵亡
You men on the Solomons were lost to a broken code.

99
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:15,220
在所罗门碰到过印地安人吗?
Tell me something. You ever run into any Indians on the Solomons?

100
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:18,350
- 印地安人，长官？ - 正确的说，应该是纳瓦荷人
- Indians, sir? - Navajo, to be exact.

101
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:23,100
军方用他们的语言，发展出一套新密码
The Corps has developed a new code based on their language.

102
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,140
评价相当不错
It's had quite an impact.

103
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:29,260
所以海军总部下令全力保护它
So much so the navy have decided to go to great lengths to protect it.

104
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,580
这就是找你来的原因
That's why you're here.

105
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:35,750
你将与密码战士配对，全力保护他们
You're to pair with one of them, keep his ass safe.

106
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:39,080
你负责保护他们的性命，以利他们执行密码任务
Your job is to keep him alive so he can do his job.

107
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:43,490
抱歉，我的专长是屠杀日军
Begging the major's pardon, but I believe I'd best serve the Corps killing Japs,

108
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:45,520
不是照顾印地安人
not baby-sitting some Indian.

109
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:48,460
我们不是随便挑到你的
Enders, we didn't pick your name out of a hat.

110
00:17:49,230 --> 00:17:51,200
我们需要的是杰出陆战队员
We need good marines.

111
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,890
所以才选上你
That's why you're standing here.

112
00:17:54,530 --> 00:17:56,800
你看
Take a look.

113
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:59,030
他就是个纳瓦荷人…应该死了
It's a Navajo. Or it was.

114
00:17:59,210 --> 00:18:03,070
遭日军逼问密码，严刑拷打致死
Tortured to death by Japanese intelligence trying to bust our code.

115
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:06,610
所幸，他想说也说不出所以然
Fortunately, he couldn't help them even if he wanted to.

116
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:10,310
- 长官？ - 他是纳瓦荷人但不是密码战士
- Sir? - Man's a Navajo, not a codetalker.

117
00:18:10,450 --> 00:18:14,010
密码由他们的语言编成，但毕竟还是密码
Code's based on their language, but it is still a code.

118
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:19,090
东条巴不得活捉一个密码战士
Tojo would like nothing more than to catch a live one.

119
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:24,290
我以下的话，绝不能泄漏出去
What I'm about to tell you, Corporal, cannot leave this room.

120
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:31,530
不管在任何情况下，密码战士绝不能落入敌人手中
Under no circumstances can you allow your codetalker to fall into enemy hands.

121
00:18:32,610 --> 00:18:35,510
你的任务是保护密码
Your mission is to protect the code...

122
00:18:37,310 --> 00:18:39,210
不惜任何代价
at all costs.

123
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:42,450
懂我的意思吗？
You understand me?

124
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,880
是的，长官，我懂
Yes, sir, I do.

125
00:18:47,450 --> 00:18:48,650
很好
Good.

126
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:51,350
恭喜你，你刚获升中士
Congratulations. You just made sergeant.

127
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:44,910
手臂保持垂直
Keep those hands vertical.

128
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,910
不错，阿兵哥
Way to go, marine.

129
00:19:53,020 --> 00:19:54,850
佛第诺，接替我一下
Fortino, take over.

130
00:19:57,460 --> 00:20:00,950
少校办公室外的是你，对吧？
Hey... That was you, right, sitting in front of the major's office?

131
00:20:01,090 --> 00:20:03,290
我叫彼得韩德森
Yeah. Listen, I'm Pete Henderson.

132
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:08,030
他们叫我公牛 不是因为我的肌肉
They call me Ox. Not cos of my big muscles or anything.

133
00:20:08,170 --> 00:20:12,260
是因为我住在加州公牛城 好莱坞北边一点点
I'm from Oxnard, California. Just north of Hollywood a ways.

134
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:15,400
你也是两栖作战通讯连的人?
So you're with JASCO too, huh?

135
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:21,670
请问两栖通讯二分队怎么走?
Hey, know where we might find 2nd Joint Assault Signal?

136
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:22,080
请问两栖通讯二分队怎么走?
Hey, know where we might find 2nd Joint Assault Signal?

137
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:24,380
没听说过,老土
No fuckin' idea, mac.

138
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:27,520
多谢
Thanks. Thanks a bunch.

139
00:20:30,890 --> 00:20:34,590
从没看过那么多白人
I've never seen so many white men.

140
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:40,060
他们也没看过那么多纳瓦荷人
They've never seen so many Navajo.

141
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,600
看起来你上过战场
Looks to me like you got to see a little action there.

142
00:20:47,570 --> 00:20:49,340
我也是
Me too.

143
00:20:50,410 --> 00:20:52,740
屁股挨了日本鬼子的子弹
Jap sons of bitches shot me right in the ass.

144
00:20:52,850 --> 00:20:55,970
相不相信? 并不是我想逃避上前线
You believe that shit? I wasn't running or nothin'.

145
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:04,990
你在两栖通讯的任务 跟这些纳瓦荷通信兵有关吗?
So, your duty with JASCO have anything to do with these Navajo radiomen?

146
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:09,550
我奉命守密
I'm not at liberty to say.

147
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,260
我发现你升官了,我也是
I see you got a new stripe there. Me too.

148
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:20,800
我猜,你不能说的秘密 跟我不能说的是一样
So I'm guessing the orders you can't tell me are the same orders I can't tell you.

149
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:22,570
了不起的任务吧?
Hell of a thing, huh?

150
00:21:22,710 --> 00:21:25,300
身不由己,中士,这里是军队
Ain't a democracy, Sergeant. It's the marines.

151
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,140
他们看起来蛮正常的
They look pretty normal, I guess.

152
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,620
难道他们得喷上迷彩?
Expecting them to wear war paint?

153
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:42,860
或许该过去打个招呼 他们好像迷路了
Maybe we ought to go introduce ourselves. They look a little lost to me.

154
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:46,620
韩德森
Henderson.

155
00:21:47,430 --> 00:21:49,400
我不想跟他们太亲近
I wouldn't get too friendly.

156
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,210
怎么样?
How!

157
00:21:57,610 --> 00:21:59,440
开个玩笑,我叫公牛
Just kiddin'. I'm Ox.

158
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,240
我叫白马
Whitehorse.

159
00:22:01,380 --> 00:22:03,250
他姓亚吉,叫班
This is Yahzee. Ben.

160
00:22:06,490 --> 00:22:08,390
-下一位 -漂亮
- Next. - Beautiful. Beautiful.

161
00:22:08,550 --> 00:22:11,750
闭着眼睛会比较好吃 下一个是谁?
Close your eyes. It'll taste better. Who's next?

162
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:52,860
可以一起吃吗?
Mind if I join you?

163
00:22:53,670 --> 00:22:57,400
我叫班亚吉,跟你同一组
I'm Ben Yahzee. Guess the Corps paired us up.

164
00:22:58,270 --> 00:23:00,030
你好吗?
How you doin'?

165
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:02,900
你挡住我的视线了
You're blocking my view.

166
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:08,080
对不起
Oh, sorry.

167
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:12,850
这难吃的东西是什么?
What do they call this crap anyway?

168
00:23:13,020 --> 00:23:14,990
军方称之为食物
Marines call it chow.

169
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:20,550
有广告不实的嫌疑哦
Well, there's a propaganda effort.

170
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:32,970
对不起,我的赔你
Sorry. You can have mine.

171
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:35,600
啊,糟糕
Shit.

172
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:44,920
你说你叫什么名字,二兵?
What'd you say your name was again, Private?

173
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:47,250
我叫班亚吉
It's Yahzee. Ben Yahzee.

174
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:50,650
端着
Hold this.

175
00:24:08,470 --> 00:24:10,140
可恶
Shit.

176
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:15,250
你的白人搭档怎么样？
How's your white man?

177
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,680
饥饿
Hungry.

178
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,820
我再玩几把
I'm in for a couple more.

179
